HEADWORD: Studdery
<hw>Stud"der*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A stud, or
collection of breeding horses and mares; also, a place for keeping a
stud.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>King Henry the Eighth erected a noble <qex>studdery</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Holinshed.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Studding</ent>⟦br⟧
